    "wikitext": {
      "*": "{{Chapter Box\n| title = Why the Log Pose is Dome-Shaped\n| jname = 「記録指針」が丸い理由\n| rname = Rogu Pōsu ga Marui Wake\n| ename = Why the Log Pose Is Dome-Shaped\n}}\n\n'''Chapter 218''' is titled \"Why the Log Pose is Dome-Shaped\".\n\n==Cover Page==\n[[Hatchan's Sea-Floor Stroll]], Vol. 32: \"Impromptu Grand Opening! The Legendary [[Takoyaki 8|Takoyaki Stand]]\".\n\nWith [[Camie]] and [[Pappag]] as helpers, [[Hatchan]] begins serving [[Foods#Takoyaki|takoyaki]] by the dozen to the starving [[Headband Catfish Village|catfish villagers]].\n\n==Short Summary==\nIn the [[Tomb of the Kings|royal crypt]], [[Nico Robin]] had lost the will to live when her dream to know about the [[Void Century|true history]] was not realized. But [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] saved her anyway by taking her away from the crumbling room. As a payback, she asks them to join their crew. Robin is interviewed by the [[Straw Hat Pirates|Straw Hats]] in order to know if their former enemy can become one of their crew. Being a clever woman, she succeeds easily. But this is not the end of the surprises for the crew; a [[St. Briss|giant ship]] then suddenly falls from the sky. After recovering from their emotions, [[Nami]] realizes that the [[Log Pose#Paradise|log pose]] is pointing up.\n\n==Long Summary==\nIn an attempt to convince the [[Straw Hat Pirates]] to let her join their crew, [[Nico Robin]] recounts the events in the crumbling [[Tomb of the Kings]]. She rolled an antidote for [[Nefertari Cobra|Cobra]] to give to [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]], who had collapsed from [[Crocodile]]'s [[poison]] after defeating him. She expressed hope that Luffy would be able to recover. Cobra then asked her why she had lied to Crocodile about what the [[Poneglyph]] said, as it actually was about the [[Pluton]] and not about the [[Arabasta Kingdom]]'s history like she claimed. Cobra realized that if she had told Crocodile the truth, the [[Seven Warlords of the Sea|Warlord]]'s [[Operation Utopia|plan]] would have certainly succeeded. Robin replied that she did not care about Arabasta or any country, and her goal had been to find the Poneglyph containing the [[Void Century|true history]]. Robin slumped in defeat that this was all for nothing, despite Cobra's attempts to reassure her. Suddenly, a healed Luffy picked them up and carried them out of the crumbling room. Robin protested for Luffy to leave her because she had nothing left to live for, but Luffy refused.\n\nSince Luffy made her carry on with life, Robin claims that she should be a Straw Hat. Luffy agrees, to the shock of his crew. Robin tells the Straw Hats about how she has associated with various villains to protect herself, citing her specialty as [[assassin]]ation. [[Usopp]] gets very scared, but Robin distracts Luffy and [[Tony Tony Chopper|Chopper]] by using her [[Hana Hana no Mi|devil fruit powers]] to tickle them. [[Nami]] swears to remain on guard against her, until Robin shows her some jewels. With [[Sanji]] immediately entranced by Robin and Usopp entranced by Robin's powers, [[Roronoa Zoro]] finds himself the only one on guard.\n\nSuddenly, bits of something fall down on the [[Going Merry]], and the crew wonders what it is. It turns out to not be precipitation but rather a [[St. Briss|full-size galleon]] falling from the sky. While the Going Merry avoids the falling [[ship]], it is swept by a tidal wave created on impact. Some more pieces of the ship fall down, including a skeleton. While the Straw Hats wonder how this could have happened, Nami finds that the [[Log Pose#Paradise|Log Pose]] is pointing up, worrying her. However, Robin states that the Log Pose must be pointing to a [[Sky Island|sky island]].\n\n==Quick Reference==\n===Chapter Notes===\n*The events in [[Alubarna]] royal palace's underground after [[Crocodile]]'s defeat are revealed in a flashback.\n**[[Nico Robin]] gave an antidote for [[Nefertari Cobra|Cobra]] to use to save [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] from [[Crocodile]]'s [[poison]] hook.\n**Robin lied about the contents in the [[Poneglyph]], which was in fact about the [[Ancient Weapons|ancient weapon]] [[Pluton]]. Her true goal was to find a Poneglyph containing the [[Void Century|true history]] of the [[world]].\n**After recovering, Luffy saved Cobra and Robin from the crumbling room, despite the latter's protest.\n*Robin states Luffy's crime was to save her when she wanted to die; and that his punishment is that she should join the [[Straw Hat Pirates]], which Luffy accepts.\n*More information about Robin is revealed:\n**She became an archaeologist at 8 years of age.\n**She has been on the run for 20 years and spent all her time in multiple criminal organizations prior to joining [[Baroque Works]].\n*A [[St. Briss|giant ship]] falls from the sky.\n*A [[scientist]] named [[Willie Gallon]] is mentioned.\n*The [[Log Pose#Paradise|log pose]] strangely points up and Robin deduces that it must be pointing towards a [[Sky Island]].\n*This is the first chapter of the [[Jaya Arc]] and the [[Sky Island Saga]].\n\n===Characters===\n{| class=\"CharTable\"\n! [[Pirate]]s\n! Citizens\n! [[Baroque Works]]\n|-\n|\n;[[Straw Hat Pirates]]\n*[[Monkey D. Luffy]]\n*[[Roronoa Zoro]]\n*[[Nami]]\n*[[Usopp]]\n*[[Sanji]]\n*[[Tony Tony Chopper]]\n*[[Nico Robin]]\n----\n;[[Arlong Pirates]]\n*[[Hatchan]] (cover)\n|\n;[[Sea Floor]]\n*[[Camie]] (cover)\n*[[Pappag]] (cover)\n----\n;[[Arabasta Kingdom]]\n*[[Nefertari Cobra]] (flashback)\n|\n*[[Crocodile]] (flashback)\n|}\n\n==Author Comment==\n{{WSJ Comment}}\n\n==Trivia==\n*A One Piece quote is written in this chapter, while the [[St. Briss|giant ship]] falls from the sky: \"Everything that humans can imagine is a possibility in reality\" Physicist [[Scientist#Willie Gallon|Willie Gallon]]. This physicist is probably invented since there are no references concerning him.\n\n==Site Navigation==\n{{Jaya Arc}}\n{{Hatchan's Sea-Floor Stroll}}\n[[ca:Capítol 218]]\n[[de:〝Logpose〟 ga marui Wake]]\n[[it:Capitolo 218]]"
